filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah. I guess so.
Maybe he found you flip-flop.
Whoa! Is this porn? What did I do? I must’ve hit something on the remote.
No, we didn’t even pay our cable bill—maybe this is how they punish us.
Yeah, so no one touches the remote. And no one touches the TV!
Imagine a protective porn bubble if you will, okay?
Hey.
Pheebs! You’re blocking the porn! Look out!
Yeah right.
Yeah, he likes porn.
Hey!
Yeah, what were you trying to get her to do?!
You play hard to get.
Then you go to Tokyo.
Way to be strong, man!

Oh yeah, sure, that makes sense. Yeah. ‘Cause you already told her you love her and she didn’t say it back, then she called you and told you that there’s another guy, so yeah, go to London that’ll scare her!
Hey.
Same kind of thing happened to me! Woman pizza delivery guy come over, gives me the pizza, takes the money, and leaves!
Noo! Nothing!
I think you’re right.
One.
That’s kinda nice.
Yeah.
Yeah.
Yeah!!
Hey, what is with the secrecy Phoebe? Huh? And what about this Denise, is she cute?
Hey Rach, listen I was thinkin’ uh, I’m gonna have an extra room over at my place…
Yeah, why don’t you move in with me? It’ll be great! We could stay up late, watch movies, and you know about Naked Thursday’s right?
Hey, what’s up?
Whoa!! Now look, don’t be just blurtin’ stuff out. I want you to really think about your answers. Okay?
Oh don’t listen to him, he’s just some guy who really wants the apartment, but I don’t think he’s gonna get it.
Umm, listen, Ross do you really think this moving in with Rachel is a good idea?
Yeah well, maybe you should go back! Okay? Rachel moves in, and before you know it you’re right where you don’t want to be! Back together!
That’s not gonna work out! Then she’s gonna come home all weepy and you’ll be tellin’ her, "Oh that’s okay. You’ll find someone." And then, bamn! She finds you!
I am telling you Ross, she is definitely gonna fall in love with you again! Now, is that what you want?
Here she comes. Hold on, I’m gonna make your life much easier.
No-no-no-no-no-no-no-no… It’s okay, I mean I—look Rach, I know I scared you off with that whole Naked Thursday’s thing, but we don’t have to do that!
Thursday’s clearly not good for ya, pick a day!
Come in. Thanks for comin’ back, umm, okay there have been a lot of people interested in the room, but I have narrowed it down and you are one of the finalists!

Okay now, before I make my final decision I uh, I just want to make sure our personalities match. Okay, so I made up a little test. Now, I’m gonna say a word and then you say the first thing that comes to mind.
Okay! Here we go. Pillow.
Very good! Okay. G.
Excellent! Okay umm, doggy.
Whoa-whoa, Treeger made you cry?
I’m gonna go down there and teach that guy a lesson.
Hey! You hold on pal! Now you made my friend, Rachel, cry. So now, you’re gonna go up there and apologize to her, unless you want me to call the landlord.
Have you heard about a little something called, Not Making Girls Cry.
I have actually not heard of that.
He said that he wasn’t gonna apologize because you guys are living here illegally, so instead what he’s gonna do is have you evicted—I’ll see you later.
Well he made Rachel cry!
All right! I’ll try! But if I can’t, you can stay with Chandler and I until you get settled.
Please don’t kick Monica and Rachel out, this wasn’t there fault, it was mine.
No you can’t do that, where would the chick and the duck live?
Noo-no-no, no, those are nicknames. I’m the chick and Chandler is the duck.
Come on man, just-just let the girls stay, I’ll do whatever you want.
Yeah-yeah, absolutely.
What, what is it?
That’s not, prison lingo, is it?
Yeah, there’s this superintendent’s dance, the Super Ball. I don’t know, and he wants to impress Marge, this lady super that he’s a crush on.
Well, he’s too shy, he doesn’t thing he’s good enough to dance with girls yet.
Aww, man, now we won’t be bank buddies!
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah! Like-like when I’m doing something exciting and I don’t wanna get too excited, I just ahh, y’know try to thing of other things like ah sandwiches, and ah baseball, and ah Chandler!
No-no, thank you.
All right, I’m here, let’s ahh, get this over with.
Whoa-whoa, don’t we need to do some kinda preparation first? Like ahh, get really drunk?
No, it’s okay, but if I’m Marge, my breasts are coming out my back.
Come on man, you’re not a potato.
What?
No I didn’t.
No, I’m not! And it wasn’t a hop it was a pademarie.
All right, well maybe I’m enjoying it a little bit. I mean I’m getting pretty good at it.
Hey-hey, hold on, this isn’t some kind of like girly dance. All right, it’s like a sport, it’s manly!
All right.
I don’t know how to lead.
What?!
Look, you wanna use our place?
We did it!!
I know, it was amazing! I mean, we totally nailed it, it was beautiful.
Oh well, okay, good luck.
Unless you wanna practice the Foxtrot again? Or-or the Tango?
Okay.
Go get ‘em Treeger.
No, I’m good.
Hey!
Ross and Rachel left us a message saying they were getting married! Isn’t that why you guys are here?
Well! What happened?! Did we miss it?
Nah, I’m too depressed to eat. I’ll probably eat in like 5 minutes. So I guess I’ll just fly home with you guys, what time’s your flight?
I don’t need that anymore.
It’ll be great! We-we could talk, and play games! Huh? This could be our chance to like renew our friendship.
Sure?
Hey.
Where is the waitress?! I’m starving!
Oh! Tell her she’s not marriage material.
Girls say it to me all the time! And believe me, if she’s anything like me, she’s just gonna be relieved.
They let you get married when you’re drunk! Most people who get married in Vegas are drunk!
An annulment? Ross! I don’t think surgery’s the answer here.
All right. All right.
Really? I don’t…
Don’t you think I asked him that before he got in?!
Ooh, I’ll play! I’ll play!

Pheebs, I am so sorry! I know I promised you a fun road trip with your friend and I didn’t deliver. But-but-but now I know that you think being awake is an important part of friendship! So, so, so I will strive to-to stay awake for as long as I know you.
Well, thank you. So, can we play 20 Questions now? I’ve got a really good one! I’ve been thinking about it since Kansas.
Yes.
That is incredible! You are the master!
What are you doing?
I’m not finished.
Hey, it's me! I'm comin' in!
Ahh, I'm gonna go get some chicken. Want some?
Okay.
You sure? Some extra crispy? Dirty rice? Beans?
All right!
Mornin' Pheebs!
Oh, he was this cab driver we had in London.
Yeah-yeah-yeah, and they had that beer! That uh…
Hey, Ross, Bodington's!
That was good beer.
Y'know, I'd walk back to London for another frosty one of those bad boys.
Hey, Pheebs!
I'll kick that door in if you give me a little sugar.
Uh, okay, Pheebs?
Umm, y'know how the other day you were talking about how you didn't get to go to London and how you were kinda feeling left out?
All right, well, we felt really bad about that so we decided we should all take a little trip together!
Yeah, all of us! All day!
Phoebe!
Mine!
Nooo, I said we needed a new plan.
Which, is the new plan!
Uh, Pheebs, you're leaking?

filename: S06E15-S06E16 That Could Have Been Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Sounds good.
Yeah?
Is it the shampoo? It’s guava.
Hey, what have you guys been up too?
Wow! You guys seem to be having a good time.
Hey that’s what all my relationships are like.
Hey, but at least you got that cool, pregnant lady glow.
Yeah, what’ going on?
Awwww!
What-what-what is so funny?
Now that’s a thinker.
A little salami.
Pastrami.
Oh! I know how you can get him, take off your bra.
There was a seen in Footloose...
Yeah-yeah, yeah, with that-that uh, plumber girl…
What? Were you like in the movie, or… Anyway, she takes off her bra under her shirt and pulls it out the sleeve. Very sexy, and classy.
If you didn’t want to play, why did you come to the party?
Phoebe, what-what are you doing?!
All right look, y’know how-y’know how when you’re dating someone and you don’t want to cheat on them, unless it’s with someone really hot?
Feel better now?
Hey, what if I said, I could even things out for ya, meatwise.
Well, I eat a lot of meat right?
Well, suppose until the baby’s born I laid off it. No extra animals would die, you-you’d just be eating my animals.
Absolutely! I could be a vegetarian. There’s no meat in beer, right?
Oooh, what you got there?
Oh-ho-ho, yeah! Hey! Y’know what goes good with that?
Ooh, I was gonna say bologna, but that’s much better. How about a little of that smoked turkey?
Ugh. Now if a cow should die of natural causes, I can have one of those right?
What?
Eyes! No, no. Your eyes! No. Chandler’s eyes!
Feminine.
Great! I’m finally getting into this sailing stuff.
Why would I do that? It took three guys to get the thing in there!
You could?
All right.
Uh, boat rope.
Uhh, rub it?
I’d say, come again. No-no, wait I-I-I know this one, I know this one, uh…
And deaf!
Yes.
I want to make a ship to shore call to Chandler.
Oh uh, I don’t know the boat way to say this, but uh never!
Because! You’re mean on the boat!
Well, lesson learned! Rachel is mean!
Does a good teacher say, "Put down the beer pinhead!?"
Six and a half! You knocked that last one out of my hand! Remember?
Well it hit me anyway! And it would’ve hurt a lot less if I had finished that last beer.
You won’t boss me around anymore?
And you’ll be nice?
And you’ll be topless?
Do you want me to learn?!
Ohh yeah.
Nope.
I don’t know why you just don’t say left.
Huh?
Uh, wow, you just said a bunch of stuff I didn’t know there.
Oh, y’know, when we did that was when that bird was flying overhead with the fish in his mouth. Did you see it? It was gross!
All right that’s it! You’re yelling and I don’t see you taking your top off! I quit!
Why not?!
Greens? I’m a Tribbiani! And Tribbianis quit!
Yes! Yes! You did and you’re still yelling at me!
Well, hey I did learn.
Yeah! Come on.
Damnit!
Just pull on it.
What else?
Thank you.
What are you doing?
What you—don’t hold it like that! You’re lettin’ all the good stuff fall out.
Hey!
No.
Cool!
That's great! Hey, can you cast me in it?
Oh! Any word on casting yet?
What do you mean? Rach, don't I seem like a professor you'd buy some kind of e-crap from?
Just watch it, and if you don't like it, you don't pass it on to your bosses!
Just pass it to your boss!
What's up?
Look, it's one thing not to cast me, but to lie to me?
Keep going Pinocchio!
You still here?
I got it from Monica. She sold it to me for a very reasonable price.
But it's an original Buffay...
Hey? what? what? wey! whoo! what? what!?
GET THAT LEGLESS WITCH OUT OF HERE!
That's not the point Chandler. The point is that you lied.
Now, what do you say?
And?... AND?
Gladys?
You're mean!
Ooh, sorry. Sorry. You finish, go.
I’m gonna be on two TV shows!
Oh, you weren’t finished?
Uh Rach, if you’re gonna start another story, at least let me finish mine.
Well, these really are the days of our lives.
Well, since you ask. They want me back on Days of Our Lives!
I’ll be playing Drake Remoray’s twin brother, Stryker!
Hey Terry!
It’s been a while, huh? Wow, it’s funny these halls look smaller then they used to.
So! Stryker Remoray huh? When do you want me to start?
Okay.
Well, I was Dr. Drake Remoray, Stryker’s twin brother. I mean, who looks more me than me right?
Hey.
Was she happy you gave her the job?
Why would they do that?! It was a good show right?!
How could this happen to me?! Yesterday I had two TV shows! Today, I got nothin’!
Uh, well they might be a little mad at me over there.
Well maybe I got a little upset and maybe I told them where they could go.
Because they wanted me to audition!
Hey! Terry.
Wait! Terry! Wait—Look—Wait I-I… Look, I’m really sorry about before. I was an idiot thinking I’m too big to audition for you. You gotta give me another chance.
Wait! Terry! Please! Look, I just lost my other job. Okay? You have no idea how much I need this. Please, help me out, for old times sake.
Nothing! It was something.
Yeah, that’s sad. Mashuga nut?
Oh my God Pheebs! You’re gonna have a baby?
Whoa, wait a minute. Who’s the father?
Well who is this guy?! Huh? Who is he? ‘Cause I will track him down and kick his ass!
Okay.
Oh good, uh you’re here. Uh Pheebs? Listen uh sit down. I-I got something I want to say.
Why?! Why can’t she marry me?!
Oh my God.
Ohh… I wonder if that dude.
Yeah.
The guy left this.
Well, I don’t know. I think it does something to salami.
Yeah. What-what did Tag say?
Hey Rach listen, no matter what this guy says I want you to know you’re not gonna be alone in this.
Pheebs, give me the ring back!
Uh yeah. Pheebs, listen about that. I only offered…
There you go!
Well, I know what I’m giving you for Christmas.
Ohhh!
Hey, Mon! I’m not doing anything, why don’t you fire me?
Good enough to get fired.
Hey! That must be why I got fired last week! Does this Orson Wells guy direct Burger King commercials?
What are you talking about? Lots of things rhyme with Rachel. Bagel. Mail. Jail. Bail. Able. May-pole.
Sure! Where are the seats?
Now, wait a second! You make food and robots?
Yeah, lady, I do! I got a problem with that!
Oh, what are you gonna do? You’re gonna fire me?
It’s still a tiny bit on fire there.
Yeah. Listen uh, I’d prefer it if you didn’t call me Joey. Since I don’t know anyone here, I thought it’d be cool to try out a cool work nickname.
No ma’am.
And I gotta pay rent! Look, how-how about this? You don’t fire me, instead I stay here, I gain their trust, and they’ll start listening to all the nice things I’ve been saying about you.
Well nothing yet, they really hate you and I want to fit in.
You bet I do! I just ah, wasn’t listening then, that’s all.
What are you gonna do? You’re gonna fire me?
Well I guess I should’ve thought about my wife and kids before I talked back to chef Geller!
Yep! Looks like it’s gonna be a leeeeean Christmas at the Dragon house this year.
We have a half hour.
Relax Ross, we'll be ready. It only takes us two minutes to get dressed.
Hey, Ross, want some cider?
Glass of fat?
What's a matter Ross? What you're nervous about your speech?
Am I in it?
Whoa!
What?
How is this your seat?
But then you left.
What's the big deal, sit somewhere else.
All right! You can have the chair.
I'm so sorry.
Me too. In fact, I think I might be a little too comfortable.
Monica, how are you gonna do that?
Hey, you can't say you're breezy, that, that totally negates the breezy.
Now she sounded breezy.
You said I had to give you the chair, you didn't say anything about the cushions.
That's right! I'm taking the essence.
Because, I'm not wearing any underwear now.
It's a rented tux. Okay. I'm not gonna go commando in another man's fatigues.
Okay, you hide my clothes. I'm gonna do the exact opposite to you.
Okay, buddy-boy. Here it is. You hide my clothes, I'm wearing everything you own.
Look at me! I'm Chandler! Could I be wearing any more clothes? Maybe if I wasn't going commando...
Yeah, Ross, way to ruin it. I was just going to get dressed.
You could drink the fat.
Yaaaay!
Let's see what else he'll do!
Right! And when is that due?
And that’s every month?
Ahhh.
No-no! No way! Joey Tribbiani does not take charity…anymore.
No! Forget it! Okay—I mean thanks, but I’m done taking money from you. All right, I can take of myself. Now, what’s next? Come on.
This is how much we pay for electric?!!!
Hey!
I don’t know Ross, not if you’re gonna talk about how you gave up a career in basketball to become a paleontologist.
Here it is! Our last pizzas together as roommates.
Oh that’s okay. Hey, actually in a way it’s kinda nice. Me, bringing the food of my ancestors, you, the food of yours!
What, are you crazy? You haven’t beaten me once since my injury plagued ’97 season. It would be easier if you just give me your money.
Okay, you’re on.
You serious?
Okay, get ready to owe me!
Okay, here we go. Ready?
This sucks man! The last night you’re here and I lose the two most important things in my life, the foosball table and $500.
Nah, not my game.
Well, what’s it called?
I don’t know how to play Cups.
All right.
A two and a five.
Really?!
A four and a nine.
No. Why?
Damn! I am good at Cups!
Well, what did you have?
Yeah.
What?
Really?
Hey!
Ross and I were helping the girls pack, took a little break, I lost $1,500 to him in Cups!

The same way you lost. I started out with a King and a Queen, bamn! Ross gets a 2 and a 3. Then I get a Jack and a King, boom! Ross gets a 4 and a 5! Ross was getting the Cup card, the D-Cup, the Sittin’ Down Bonus! Meanwhile, I didn’t even get half a cup! Nothin’!!
And he never played before either! Y’know what I think? I think beginner’s luck, very important in Cups.
It’s him, not it!
Wait a second, I see what you’re trying to do here! You-you’re trying to give me money again!

I will be okay! Look Chandler, you gotta get it out of your head that I can’t take care of myself. Okay? Look, I’m not gonna miss you helping me out with money. The only thing that I’m gonna miss…is you. And now the dog.
